name: Class of 2029 (Freshmen)
description: The official unofficial group for all 1st year students. Find roommates, ask about orientation, and meet people in your dorms.

name: Engineering Study circle
description: An informal study group for engineering students struggling with calculus and physics. We meet in the library basement.

name: Commuter Students
description: Do you drive or bus to campus? Join us to coordinate carpools, discuss traffic, and find the best parking spots.

name: International Students Hub
description: A welcoming space for students from abroad. Visa advice, cultural exchange, and finding food from home.

name: Women in STEM
description: Support network for women in Science, Tech, Engineering, and Math. Mentorship and coffee chats.

name: Late Night Library Crew
description: For the night owls who stay on campus past midnight. Safety in numbers and study motivation.

name: Grad Student Lounge
description: A space for Masters and PhD students to complain about thesis writing and find coffee.

name: Mature Students Association
description: Connecting students who are returning to school later in life. A supportive community for those balancing family, work, and studies.

name: LGBTQ+ & Allies
description: A safe and inclusive space for queer students and allies. Weekly hangouts, advocacy, and social events.

name: Transfer Student Connect
description: New to campus but not new to college? Connect with other transfer students to navigate credits and find friends.

name: Student Parents Network
description: Resources and playdates for students who are also raising children. Share babysitting tips and study hacks.

name: Campus Musicians Jam
description: Looking for a drummer, bassist, or vocalist? Join our jam sessions. All genres from jazz to metal welcome.

name: Gym Rats & Fitness
description: Find a gym buddy, spotter, or running partner. We discuss workout routines, nutrition, and lifting goals.

name: Sustainable Fashion & Thrifting
description: For students who love vintage clothes, upcycling, and swapping outfits. Sustainability and style combined.

name: Blockchain & Crypto
description: Discussions on Bitcoin, Ethereum, and Web3 technology. Not financial advice, just tech enthusiasm.

name: Student Entrepreneurs
description: Building a startup? Find co-founders, pitch ideas, and network with business minded students.

name: Pre-Med Support Group
description: MCAT study sessions, med school application advice, and shadowing opportunities for future doctors.

name: Pre-Law Society
description: LSAT prep and mock trials. Connect with others aiming for law school and legal careers.

name: Creative Writers & Poets
description: Share your poetry, short stories, and novels. Weekly writing sprints and feedback workshops.

name: Campus Photographers
description: For anyone with a camera or iPhone who loves taking photos. Photo walks and editing tips.

name: Weekend Hikers (Casual)
description: Easy to moderate hikes for getting fresh air. No intense gear required, just good vibes and nature.

name: Campus Foodies
description: Exploring the best cheap eats around campus. We organize group dinners and bubble tea runs.

name: Casual Gamers
description: Looking for people to play LoL, Valorant, Minecraft, or Mario Kart? casual matches and watch parties.

name: K-Pop Dance & Stan Group
description: Learning dance covers and discussing latest comebacks. For fans of BTS, Blackpink, NewJeans, and more.

name: Mindfulness & Meditation
description: Weekly guided meditation and stress relief sessions. Take a break from exams and breathe.

name: Volunteer Corps
description: Find opportunities to give back to the local community. Charity events, food drives, and cleanups.

name: Peer Tutors Network
description: Students helping students. If you aced a class, offer help here. If you are failing, find help here.

name: Buy & Sell Marketplace
description: The place to sell old textbooks, furniture, and electronics to other students on campus.

name: Lost & Found
description: Did you lose your water bottle or keys? Post it here. A community effort to return lost items.

name: Car Enthusiasts
description: For those who love cars, modifications, and mechanics. Meetups in the south parking lot.

name: Pet Owners on Campus
description: Do you have a dog or cat in your apartment? Organize dog walks and share pet care tips.

name: Tabletop RPG & D&D
description: Dungeons and Dragons campaigns, Warhammer, and Pathfinder. Looking for Dungeon Masters and players for weekend sessions.
